snippet.textDisplay:
I watch off the ranch to pretty much see the perfect life of a guy in his 30’s should have. A family, big house, successful businesses, a lot of guns.

I just like to remind myself what I might have had if I hadn’t wasted so much time not caring about my future. Now i’m getting old and the possibility of ever getting a picture perfect life like this is very slim. I hope matt appreciates all of that. He definitely worked for a lot of his success, but he was lucky enough to have a dad to learn from, and kind of get a start from dad’s example and assets. Ppl don’t realize how important it is to have a dad that pretty much hands down a business to you and has land to share. That alone gives you a HUGE advantage, and a start in life. Getting all that stuff from scratch is much harder. Not saying Matt just was given free shit but he definitely had a lot of help getting his whole life started and a dad to give him stuff.

Ok, so here come the 10 year old fanboys to start emotionally defending a famous person that doesn’t even know them. Never will I understand why there are so many fame nut huggers. If they are a fan, they will froth at the mouth attacking anyone who makes any kind of comment that could be construed as negatives. Cone on fanboys, hurry, before your mom comes in and tells you it’s time for bed, then tucks you in.
